 Erkin Rehim shows cotton harvested in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Oct. 15, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge) YULI, Nov. 3 (Xinhua) -- Erkin Rehimc is a cotton farmer from Yuli, a county in the southern part of Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, China's largest cotton-growing area. Xinjiang has encouraged cotton farmers to apply modern agricultural machinery to boost the development of the industry in recent years. Once a shepherd and a restaurant owner, Erkin Rehimc began growing cotton in 2004 and has benefited from agricultural mechanization since 2017. This year, the 49-year-old cotton farmer uses cotton pickers to harvest his 550 mu (about 90.6 acres) of cotton fields in 24 hours. "We can expect a bumper harvest this year," he said.  Erkin Rehim prepares to go to a labour market to find workers to help trim cotton plants in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, July 18, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)  Erkin Rehim (L) tries to find workers willing to pick up cotton at a labour market in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Oct. 20, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)  Erkin Rehim (L) and his wife cook at home in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Oct. 26, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)  Erkin Rehim (R) and his daughter eat noodles at home in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, July 18, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)  Combo photo shows Erkin Rehim picking cotton on Oct. 15, 2021 (top) and trimming cotton plants on July 18, 2021 (below) in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)  Erkin Rehim (L, back) asks his relatives to help pick cotton in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Oct. 20, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)  Erkin Rehim (R) discuss the harvest plan with a cotton picker service supplier in his field in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Oct. 24, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)  Erkin Rehim (R) and his wife watch a cotton picker working in one of his fields in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Oct. 24, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)  Aerial photo taken on Oct. 24, 2021 shows cotton pickers working in one of farmer Erkin Rehim's fields in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)  A cotton picker works in one of farmer Erkin Rehim's fields in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Oct. 24, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)  A cotton picker works in one of farmer Erkin Rehim's fields in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Oct. 24, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)  Erkin Rehim (R) and his relatives put hand-picked cotton into bags in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Oct. 22, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)  Erkin Rehim delivers his cotton to a factory in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Oct. 22, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)  Erkin Rehim drives a tractor to sell his cotton to a factory in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Oct. 22, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)  Erkin Rehim gets paid after selling his cotton to a factory in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Oct. 22, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)  Erkin Rehim drives home after selling his cotton to a factory in Yuli County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Oct. 22, 2021. (Xinhua/Zhao Ge)â– 